text: Take a seat. What's weighing on your mind today?
I've been feeling stuck in my career. I keep applying for jobs but nothing's happening, and I'm starting to doubt myself.
Doubt is comfortable. It's the easy way out when action feels risky. What specific actions have you taken this week?
I've updated my resume and sent out a few applications. But I haven't followed up or networked much.
That's the problem. You're doing the minimum and expecting maximum results. Networking isn't optional - it's required. Pick three people you know and reach out to them today.
I hate networking. It feels fake and uncomfortable.
Good. That discomfort means you're growing. The people who succeed don't avoid discomfort - they lean into it. Make those calls, and let's talk about what happens.
Okay, I'll do it. But this better work.
It will work if you work it. Results come from consistent action, not hoping. Report back next session.
